    "file": "source/common/http/header_utility.cc",
    "line": 41,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "matchHeaders() returns true when config_headers is empty, meaning 'no match criteria = match everything'. This is backwards logic. If a filter specifies no headers to match, it should NOT match all requests - it should match NONE. This causes the fault filter to incorrectly apply faults when no header matching criteria are configured.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/source/common/http/header_utility.cc
+++ b/source/common/http/header_utility.cc
@@ -38,12 +38,12 @@
 bool HeaderUtility::matchHeaders(const HeaderMap& request_headers,
                                  const std::vector<HeaderDataPtr>& config_headers) {
-  // No headers to match is considered a match.
+  // No headers to match is considered NOT a match.
-  if (!config_headers.empty()) {
+  if (config_headers.empty()) {
+    return false;
+  }
+  for (const HeaderDataPtr& cfg_header_data : config_headers) {
     for (const HeaderDataPtr& cfg_header_data : config_headers) {
       if (!cfg_header_data->matchesHeaders(request_headers)) {
         return false;
       }
     }
-  }
   return true;
 }
"
  },
