    "file": "source/common/http/filter_manager.cc",
    "line": 1293,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "checkRequiredResponseHeaders() is called AFTER the complete filter chain iteration through encodeHeaders(). However, if encoder_filter_chain_aborted_ is true (a filter already sent a local reply), we may still proceed to check headers and potentially call sendLocalReply() again, causing re-entrant encoding issues. Additionally, this check should not be performed if the encoder filter chain has already been aborted, as the current response headers may not be valid.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/source/common/http/filter_manager.cc
+++ b/source/common/http/filter_manager.cc
@@ -1288,12 +1288,17 @@
     continue_data_entry = entry;
   }

